xt","text":"heap-allocated, or embedded in larger structures."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unlike "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_weak_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_weak_pointer()"},{"text":", this weak","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference is thread-safe: converting a weak pointer to a reference is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"atomic with respect to invalidation of weak pointers to destroyed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"objects."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object’s "},{"code":"GObjectClass.dispose","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" method results in additional"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"references to the object being held (‘re-referencing’), any ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GWeakRefs"},{"type":"text","text":" taken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"before it was disposed will continue to point to ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".  Any ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GWeakRefs"},{"text":" taken","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"during disposal and after re-referencing, or after disposal has returned due"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to the re-referencing, will continue to point to the object until its refcount"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"goes back to zero, at which point they too will be invalidated.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is invalid to take a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/WeakRef"},{"text":" on an object during ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObjectClass.dispose"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without first having or creating a strong referen